@startuml
!include ../includes/appsec-style.puml
title AppSec Process 08: IAST Verified Vulnerabilities (Seeker)

' Purpose: Use runtime instrumentation to produce verified findings with low false-positive rates.

start

partition "Instrument" {
  :Deploy Seeker agent to test/QA;
  :Register application with AppCode;
}

partition "Exercise App" {
  :Run functional/integration tests;
  :Optional targeted security tests;
}

partition "Detect" {
  :Seeker identifies runtime vulnerability;
  if (Seeker verified?) then (Yes)
    :Mark as VERIFIED;
  else (No)
    :Route for manual validation;
  endif
}

partition "Triage & Track" {
  :Correlate to AppCode + owner;
  :Create/Update ticket with evidence;
  :Set SLA by severity;
}

partition "Remediate & Verify" {
  :Fix and redeploy;
  :Re-run tests to confirm closure;
}

note right
Key message: **Verified findings reduce triage noise**.
AppCode keeps runtime findings tied to release trains.
end note

stop
@enduml
